Adversarial review (review-1.json):
  Opus 4.7 via Agent tool; verdict: ship; 0 blockers; 3 nits.
  Nits:
    - last_edited_time-based "page-added" trigger fires on edits
      too (spec-literal behavior; downstream consumers should know)
    - PAGE_CAP=50 silent cap if Notion's response is unexpectedly
      huge; would benefit from a warn log when cap exits
    - initialState ignores its args parameter (harmless)

Notes / decisions:
  - Three adapters in one file: keeps the notion-specific helpers
    (callTool wrapper, maxIso, pagination shape) shared without
    needing a sub-module. Each adapter is small enough to read in
    one screen.
  - Notion's API uses start_cursor (snake_case) for pagination
    input, next_cursor + has_more for output. Adapter normalizes
    accordingly.
  - HTTP errors + successful=false envelope both throw cleanly so
    cron-kicker's circuit breaker counts them.
  - Defensive recovery on missing lastSeen (any of the three) →
    silent re-baseline at now(), zero events. Matches F.5/F.6.
  - Boundary-id reset semantics: when newHighWater advances past
    lastSeen, replace lastSeenIds with IDs at the new high-water.
    When newHighWater === lastSeen, merge old+new so previously-
    emitted boundary rows stay deduped indefinitely. Same pattern
    as F.5 fix cycle.

